    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="sal.00001.001_large.jpg.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="sal.00001.002_large.jpg.jpg" type="verso"/>

            <opener>  
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street<ptr target="sal.00001_n5"/></name>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1884-11-18" rend="right">Nov. 18 '84<!--<ptr target="sal.00001_n1"
                        />--></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Yours of yesterday just rec'd&#8212;with the $25&#8212;(making 150 in all)<ptr
                    target="sal.00001_n2"/>&#8212;best thanks&#8212;So you like the Brignoli bit<ptr
                    target="sal.00001_n3"/>&#8212;I was not sure it amounted to much, but it came
                from the heart&#8212;(it was first sent to the <hi rend="italic">Tribune</hi> to be
                published the morning of B's funeral, but the T sent it back)&#8212;</p>
            <p>How are you all? How is Al, under the new dispensation? I send my love specially to
                Alma and the girls &#38; the new Mrs J&#8212;</p>
            <p>Nothing very new with me&#8212;I am ab't as well as usual except an increasing
                lameness&#8212;Anticipate a time not remote when I shall be unable to walk at
                all&#8212;Have not forgotten the <hi rend="italic">Memorandum History of the
                    Portrait</hi>&#8212;have already outlined &#38; partly prepared it&#8212;you
                shall have it soon<ptr target="sal.00001_n4"/>&#8212;</p>
            <p>I am writing this up in my big den&#8212;the floor all around horribly <hi
                    rend="italic">litter</hi>-rary, but a cheery wood fire in the little
                stove&#8212;&#38; I comfortable in my great capacious rattan arm-chair&#8212;(which
                I may will to Al, if he cares for it)&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed>W W</signed>
            </closer>

        </body>
